  "content": "sp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#9492;&#9472; <span style=\"color: var(--accent-purple);\">#23</span> Observability &rarr; <span style=\"color: var(--accent-purple);\">#24</span> <span style=\"color: var(--accent-purple);\">#25</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <!-- Stats row -->\n  <div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n    <div class=\"stat-box\" style=\"padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 40px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-green);\">13</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 4px;\">Issues created</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat-box\" style=\"padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 40px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-amber);\">5</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 4px;\">Phases</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat-box\" style=\"padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 40px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-red);\">2</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 4px;\">High-risk flagged</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>Every issue has a prompt with specific Rust types to implement, files to modify, and test expectations. The tracking issue has the full dependency graph. This came from the design review, not manual planning.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">05 / 09</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- SLIDE 6: KNOWLEDGE PERSISTENCE -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-purple);\">Research That Compounds</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    Nothing Gets<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-purple\">Lost Between Sessions</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    Every brainstorm, every decision, every rejected alternative gets persisted. When I revisit a topic, I see what I explored before and what changed since.\n  </div>",
